#. type: Title #
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:1
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:4
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Integrated Address"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:7
#, markdown-text
msgid "Integrated addresses are ideal for accepting Monero in an automated fashion - like in online stores and exchanges."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:9
#, markdown-text
msgid "Monero integrated address embeds a payment ID. This allows you to learn for what you are being paid."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:11
#, markdown-text
msgid "Please note these are Monero technical payment IDs and must not be confused with business identifiers like order number or invoice number."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:15
#, markdown-text
msgid "The transaction to integrated address will not reveal the payment ID publicly.  Payment ID in a transaction will be encrypted with a shared secret (one-time random key known only to sender and recipient).  Only the recipient will be able to match the transaction against payment ID."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:17
#, markdown-text
msgid "Monero integrated address obsoletes the former practice of using full 32-bytes payment ID in a transaction extra field (where it was not encrypted)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:19
#, markdown-text
msgid "Data structure ([src](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/f7b9f44c1b0d53170fd7f53d37fc67648f3247a2/src/cryptonote_basic/cryptonote_basic_impl.cpp#L172)):"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:27
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"Index       | Size in bytes    | Description\n"
"------------|------------------|-------------------------------------------------------------\n"
"0           | 1                | identifies the network and address type; [19](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/793bc973746a10883adb2f89827e223f562b9651/src/cryptonote_config.h#L150) - main chain; [54](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/793bc973746a10883adb2f89827e223f562b9651/src/cryptonote_config.h#L162) - test chain\n"
"1           | 32               | public spend key\n"
"33          | 32               | public view key\n"
"65          | 8                | compact payment ID -  8 bytes randomly generated by the recipient; note that it does not need encryption in the address itself but it is hidden in a transaction paying to integrated address to prevent linking payment with the address by external observers\n"
"73          | 4                | checksum ([Keccak-f[1600] hash](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/common/base58.cpp#L261) of the previous 73 bytes, trimmed to first [4](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/common/base58.cpp#L53) bytes)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:29
#, markdown-text
msgid "It totals to 77 bytes. The bytes are then encoded ([src](https://github.com/monero-project/monero/blob/8f1f43163a221153403a46902d026e3b72f1b3e3/src/common/base58.cpp#L240)) in [Monero specific Base58](/cryptography/base58) format, resulting in a 106 chars long string. Example integrated address:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:31
#, markdown-text
msgid "`4LL9oSLmtpccfufTMvppY6JwXNouMBzSkbLYfpAV5Usx3skxNgYeYTRj5UzqtReoS44qo9mtmXCqY45DJ852K5Jv2bYXZKKQePHES9khPK`"
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:32
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Integrated addresses vs subaddresses"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:35
#, markdown-text
msgid "Both types allow you to learn for what you are being paid."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:37
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Individuals** should prefer **subaddresses** to receive payments. This is to improve privacy in certain scenarios. See article on [subaddresses](/public-address/subaddress) for details.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:39
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "**Businesses** accepting payments in an automated way should prefer **integrated addresses**. The rationale is as follows:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:41
#, markdown-text
msgid "Scenario where subaddresses improve privacy is not applicable to businesses b/c businesses have the same identity over time. Consequently, subaddresses provide no benefits over integrated addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:43
#, markdown-text
msgid "No private key is necessary to generate integrated address. This provides a strong security advantage because services that generate integrated addresses need no access to wallet. In contrast, to generate a subaddress, one needs a private view key."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:45
#, markdown-text
msgid "No shared counter is necessary to generate integrated address. This allows individual services to independently generate integrated addresses w/o synchronizing on a common sequence. In contrast, subaddresses are generated sequentially, and so the sequence (the counter or index) is a coupling point between the wallet and all services that need to generate the address. Back to integrated addresses, note that embedded payment IDs are 64-bit. This means the space is large enough that one can simply generate them randomly and reliably assume uniqueness."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:47
#, markdown-text
msgid "In very specific scenarios, preparation effort to monitor a very huge number of subaddresses, could became an issue. See [this reddit thread](https://www.reddit.com/r/Monero/comments/9aevri/is_it_fair_to_say_integrated_addresses_are/e4vf47p) for details."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:49
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Caveats"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:52
#, markdown-text
msgid "There are some caveats:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:54
#, markdown-text
msgid "Single transaction cannot pay to multiple integrated addresses."
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/public-address/integrated-address.md:56
#, markdown-text
msgid "As individual running a wallet you should generally prefer subaddresses. However, if you happen to use integrated addresses, you should allow Monero software to generate integrated addresses for you (instead of forcing your own payment IDs)."
msgstr ""

